Based on my exploration, the auth middleware already exists and is fully implemented:

**Existing Implementation:**
- `src/middleware/auth-middleware.ts` - Factory function `createAuthMiddleware` that extracts JWT from Bearer token, verifies it, checks sessions, and returns 401 for invalid/missing tokens
- `src/middleware/auth-middleware.test.ts` - Comprehensive tests covering valid tokens, missing tokens, invalid tokens, expired tokens, revoked sessions, and rate limiting
- `src/auth/withAuth.ts` - HOC that wraps route handlers with authentication, used across all protected routes

**Routes using auth:**
- `notes/route.ts`, `notes/[id]/route.ts` - withAuth
- `notifications/route.ts`, `notifications/read-all/route.ts`, `notifications/[id]/read/route.ts` - withAuth  
- `gradebook/route.ts`, `gradebook/course/[id]/route.ts` - withAuth
- `quizzes/[id]/route.ts`, `quizzes/[id]/submit/route.ts`, `quizzes/[id]/attempts/route.ts` - withAuth
- `enroll/route.ts`, `dashboard/admin-stats/route.ts`, `courses/search/route.ts` - withAuth

**Public routes (correctly unprotected):**
- `health/route.ts` - health check
- `csrf-token/route.ts` - CSRF token endpoint (uses session header, not JWT)

